BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Writers Salon Series: Roshan Sethi
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260706T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260706T190000
DTSTAMP:20260704T112059Z
UID:dartmouth-81923@free-food-dartmouth
DESCRIPTION:Original event page(s):\nhttps://home.dartmouth.edu/events/eve
 nt?event=81923\nhttps://hop.dartmouth.edu/events/roshan-sethi\n\nDescripti
 on:\nA writer\, director and oncologist\, Roshan Sethi will read from his 
 debut novel and discuss translating real-world medicine into compelling fi
 lm and television.\nAcclaimed screenwriter\, director and physician Roshan
  Sethi\, who recently joined us virtually after a screening of his latest 
 film\nA Nice Indian Boy\n\, now joins us in person to share a preview of h
 is debut novel\nThe Simp\n\, due to release this summer. This razor-sharp 
 novel charts the rise and fall of an unemployed actor who lands the greate
 st role of his life when he's hired as a personal assistant to a demanding
 \, highly absurd Hollywood family.\nRoshan is joined in conversation by Pr
 ofessor Dawn Carey\, Senior Associate Director (Global Health and Developm
 ent) for the Dickey Center for International Understanding. They will disc
 uss how Roshan has translated real-world medicine into compelling film and
  television\, from TV shows like\nThe Resident\nto the abortion drama\nCal
 l Jane\n.\nEnjoy a free drink during the event and stick around after for 
 a book signing!\nThis event is free and unticketed.\nGet more info here.\n
 \nSponsor / organizer: Hopkins Center for the Arts\n\nAudience: Public\n\n
 Source: Dartmouth\n\nWhy this was included: food keyword near service cont
 ext\n\nFood availability is inferred from the source listing\; verify deta
 ils before attending.
LOCATION:Top of the Hop\, Hopkins Center for the Arts
STATUS:CONFIRMED
URL:https://home.dartmouth.edu/events/event?event=81923
END:VEVENT
