DESCRIPTION:Original event page(s):\nhttps://home.dartmouth.edu/events/eve
 nt?event=82023\n\nDescription:\nAs a part of Xpressions of Dartmouth 2026\
 , join us for an afternoon of fun in the sun! Cookout & Canoes is a free s
 ummer event hosted at Tom Dent Cabin where you can paddle the river\, enjo
 y delicious food\, vibe to music\, and connect with the campus community. 
 We’ll have plenty of equipment available\, with special guest Alleah Sch
 weitzer from SWC to lead a mindfulness paddle\, lawn games\, EMT and safet
 y info\, and more!\nGrab a bite with options from The Box and cool down wi
 th some refreshments\, or hang out by the river with equipment courtesy of
  Ledyard Canoe Club and the Office of Pluralism & Leadership.\nThis is a p
 erfect chance to soak up summer\, meet new people\, and enjoy the outdoors
 .\nNeed resources on river/water and sun safety as we kick off summer happ
 enings on campus? We got you covered!\nHosted in collaboration with the Of
 fice of Pluralism & Leadership and campus/community partners including Led
 yard Canoe Club\, Student Wellness\, 2028 Class Council and the First Gene
 ration Office. Free and open to all Dartmouth students\, staff and faculty
 ! Dartmouth EMS will also be present for any medical or safety needs.\nCom
 e solo\, bring a friend\, or paddle with a group\, but just don’t miss i
 t!\n\nSponsor / organizer: Dartmouth Emergency Medical Services (EMS)\, Of
 fice of Pluralism and Leadership (OPAL)\, Student Wellness Center\n\nAudie
 nce: Alumni\, Faculty\, Postdoc\, Staff\, Students-Graduate\, Students-Und
 ergraduate\n\nSource: Dartmouth\n\nWhy this was included: Free Food catego
