SUMMARY:Publishing Talk: Adam Gianelli
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260716T123000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260716T133000
DTSTAMP:20260704T112059Z
UID:dartmouth-82080@free-food-dartmouth
DESCRIPTION:Original event page(s):\nhttps://home.dartmouth.edu/events/eve
 nt?event=82080\n\nDescription:\nAbout the Poet:\nAdam Giannelli is the aut
 hor of\nTremulous Hinge\n(University of Iowa PressOpens in a new window\, 
 2017)\, winner of the Iowa Poetry Prize. He is also the translator of a se
 lection of prose poems by Marosa di Giorgio\,\nDiadem\n(BOA EditionsOpens 
 in a new window\, 2012)\, which was shortlisted for the PEN Award for Poet
 ry in Translation\, and the editor of\nHigh Lonesome\n(Oberlin College Pre
 ssOpens in a new window\, 2006)\, a collection of critical essays on Charl
 es Wright. His writing has appeared in\nPoetry\, Kenyon Review\, New Engla
 nd Review\, Ploughshares\, Atlantic\, New York Times Magazine\, New Criter
 ion\,\nand elsewhere. His work has been supported by fellowships and resid
 encies from several institutions\, including the National Endowment for th
 e Arts\, Fulbright Program\, James Merrill House\, Bread Loaf Writers’ C
 onference\, Sewanee Writers’ Conference\, Yaddo\, and MacDowell. He has 
 taught at Oberlin College\, Hamilton College\, Colby College\, and Purdue 
 University.\n\nSponsor / organizer: Literary Arts Bridge\n\nAudience: Publ
 ic\n\nSource: Dartmouth\n\nWhy this was included: Free Food category\; exp
 licit food-service wording\; food or meal keyword in title/summary\n\nFood
  availability is inferred from the source listing\; verify details before 
 attending.
LOCATION:Literary Arts Bridge (7 Lebanon St. Suite 105)
STATUS:CONFIRMED
URL:https://home.dartmouth.edu/events/event?event=82080
